OL,3,CBehind closed doors at haven for women
OL,4,Cfleeing domestic abuse
OL,6,FThe boss of a domestic abuse charity
OL,7,Fwhich runs two refuges in says the
OL,8,Fgovernment must provide more long-term
OL,9,Fdedicated funding to help save the
OL,10,Flives of survivors and their children.
OL,12,FThe warning comes amid fears some
OL,13,Fservices are at risk of closing
OL,14,Fbecause of a council funding crisis,
OL,15,Fafter the Domestic Abuse Commissioner
OL,16,Fsaid many were "hanging by a thread".
OL,18,FITV News Calendar was given special
OL,19,Faccess to one of Sheffield Women's
OL,20,FAid's two refuges in the city to see
OL,21,Ftheir lifesaving work first-hand.
