OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F361A1713442808
OL,3,CBehind closed doors at haven for women
OL,4,Cfleeing domestic abuse
OL,6,F"I don't blame the councils at all. I
OL,7,Fknow that they're under pressure but
OL,8,Fwhat we have to say is if we want
OL,9,Fthese services and we want to save
OL,10,Fwomen and children's lives, they have
OL,11,Fto be adequately funded and
OL,12,Fsustainably funded as opposed to the
OL,13,Fpiecemeal short term funding that is
OL,14,Fquite often a way of life for services
OL,15,Flike Sheffield Women's Aid."
OL,17,FThe government describes domestic
OL,18,Fabuse as a "heinous crime" and said it
OL,19,Fwas providing victims and survivors
OL,20,Fthe support they need.
